## Memory Architecture

This system uses psychology-inspired multi-store memory (Atkinson-Shiffrin model):

| Store | Location | Purpose | Lifespan |
|-------|----------|---------|----------|
| Working | `working.md` | Active session log | 7-day rolling |
| Episodic | `episodes/` | Significant events with context | 60 days (access-gated) |
| Semantic | `semantic/` | Factual knowledge by domain | Permanent |
| Procedural | `procedures/` | Validated step-by-step recipes | Permanent (versioned) |

## Semantic Files (factual knowledge)
- `semantic/codebase.md` - Code patterns, architecture, conventions
- `semantic/domain.md` - Business logic, product concepts
- `semantic/tools.md` - CLI tools, build system, CI/CD
- `semantic/people.md` - Team members, roles, working patterns
- `semantic/user.md` - User preferences, work style

